    {
      "id": "edge-compatibility",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Compatibility",
      "position": {
        "x": 270,
        "y": 560
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Compatibility\n\n- persisted edges SHOULD carry explicit `sourcePort` and `targetPort`\n- the canonical default endpoint is explicit `root`\n- if endpoint ids are provided, they MUST exist on the node\n- tools and agents MUST NOT invent non-existent ports or handles\n- some runtime paths and legacy readers may still tolerate omitted ports and interpret them as `root`, but that is migration tolerance, not the preferred stored shape\n\nThe portable authoring rule is therefore: write explicit `root`, validate explicit non-root endpoints, and treat omission as legacy compatibility only.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
