    {
      "id": "edge-examples",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Examples",
      "position": {
        "x": 180,
        "y": 900
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Examples\n\n**Runtime edge typing:**\n\n`type` MAY be provided as a string runtime render primitive. It controls how the edge is drawn or routed, not the full semantic contract by itself.\n\nExamples currently in use include:\n- `reference`\n- `relates`\n- `default`\n- `straight`\n- `governs`\n\nMoving forward:\n- a plain edge remains valid without a class or type\n- if `type` is omitted, the renderer falls back to a simple line\n- when an edge class is assigned, the class may provide `defaultEdgeType`\n- an instance-level `type` override wins when both are present",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
